A fire incident has destroyed 12 shops at the Wunti Market in Bauchi metropolis. Speaking during a sympathy visit on Friday, Governor Bala Abdulkadir Mohammed expressed shock over the incident. The Governor who was represented by his deputy, Senator Baba Tela assured the victims of immediate government’s support. He said already, the State Emergency Management Agency has commenced an assessment of the damages in order to provide basic assistance. Chairman of Wunti Market, Nura Zango expressed gratitude to the governor for pledging to support the victims. DAILY POSTt gathered that no loss of lives were recorded as at the time of filing this report. Authorities say properties worth millions of naira were destroyed in the fire. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.